            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Para usar um método de classe, é o mesmo que usar uma variável de classe, exceto que precisamos adicionar parênteses. Como aqui com <code>rocky.bark()</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"class\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"Virtual_Pet\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  color = \" /><text value=\"&quot;brown&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"bark\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(self)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bark&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky = Virtual_Pet()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(rocky.color)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"rocky.bark()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"117\" endIndex=\"122\" /><option startIndex=\"122\" endIndex=\"123\" /><option startIndex=\"123\" endIndex=\"127\" /><option startIndex=\"127\" endIndex=\"128\" /><option startIndex=\"128\" endIndex=\"129\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"brown\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Bark\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>rocky</code> seguido de <code>.</code> e depois <code>bark</code>, <code>(</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
